      Elsewhere in oil
   =20
 =20
We have  talked a few  times recently about the fact that big international=
 oil companies have joint ventures in Russia and decided pretty hastily to =
exit them. Here is a Wall Street Journal story about =E2=80=9CHow Oil Giant=
s=E2=80=99 Bets on Russia, Years in the Making, Crumbled in Days.=E2=80=9D =
As we have discussed, it is one thing to say =E2=80=9Cwe are exiting our Ru=
ssia ventures=E2=80=9D and another thing to figure out how to actually do t=
hat. You can=E2=80=99t exactly sell the shares of these joint ventures=C2=
=A0on the open market, and abandoning them=C2=A0essentially means selling t=
hem to Russian companies for free. Conceptually the right approach is somet=
hing like:=09Promise to get rid of them.=09Cross them off the list of =E2=
=80=9Cassets we own=E2=80=9D and move them to a list of =E2=80=9Cassets we =
don=E2=80=99t want to own,*=E2=80=9D with a little footnote saying =E2=80=
=9C*but still technically own.=E2=80=9D=09Wait a while until things are mor=
e normal, or until you find an acceptable buyer.=09Eventually sell them for=
 some amount of money.=09Do something with the money.Obviously that is a ve=
ry schematic description. Each part is complicated but here let=E2=80=99s f=
ocus on Step 2, crossing them off one list and putting them on another list=
. That is a pretty metaphysical step; here=E2=80=99s the Journal:Lawyers, a=
ccountants and outside advisers are working to determine how the oil compan=
ies can restructure their Russian holdings. They are exploring complex opti=
ons for ring fencing them from ongoing operations=E2=80=94transferring the =
assets to separate corporate entities=E2=80=94while winding them down and t=
rying to preserve as much value as possible, some of the people close to th=
e companies said. Options include escrow accounts with shareholders named a=
s beneficiaries and special-purpose entities walled off from continuing bus=
inesses.Asset sales would be challenging, some of the people close to the c=
ompanies said. One primary goal is to avoid ceding direct control to a Russ=
ian counterpart or otherwise inadvertently benefiting Russia, they said.=E2=
=80=9CEscrow accounts with shareholders named as beneficiaries=E2=80=9D? Li=
ke, before the restructuring, BP Plc (say) would own the asset, and any val=
ue from the asset would belong to BP=E2=80=99s shareholders. After the rest=
ructuring, some entity set up by BP would own the asset, and any value from=
 the asset would belong to BP=E2=80=99s shareholders. But in some legal or =
perhaps only metaphysical sense=C2=A0BP would no longer own the asset, so i=
t could say that it was getting out of Russian oil ventures, which is the p=
oint here.This is all a bit uncharted and you have some options on what you=
 want to accomplish with this structure. Like:=09What does =E2=80=9Cshareho=
lders=E2=80=9D mean? Most simply, the escrow account would be for whoever o=
wns the company=E2=80=99s shares at any particular time; if the company sel=
ls the asset in 2023 and realizes some proceeds, it will pay out those proc=
eeds to its shareholders in 2023. But you could imagine, as it were, distri=
buting the claims to=C2=A0current=C2=A0shareholders, so that if you owned t=
he company=E2=80=99s stock in March 2022 and the asset pays out in 2023, yo=
u get a share of=C2=A0the proceeds even if you have sold your stock. (The t=
heory being that, since you owned the stock at the time the company abandon=
ed the asset at zero, you were the one hurt by that and you should get the =
money.)=09If you=E2=80=99re doing that you could make the escrow claims =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0tradable? Like, issue a tracking stock on your abandoned Russia=
n JV assets? That seems distasteful and yet somehow correct. If you want to=
 get rid of your JV assets, can=E2=80=99t sell them, and don=E2=80=99t want=
 to abandon them to your Russian partners, one move is to effectively spin =
them off to your shareholders. Then you don=E2=80=99t own them anymore, but=
 you have maximized shareholder value. And then if your shareholders don=E2=
=80=99t want to own Russian JV assets they can sell them, in indirect trada=
ble-escrow-claim form=C2=A0to someone who does. (Who is that?)=C2=A0=09Why =
shareholders? When Shell Plc=C2=A0bought=C2=A0Russian oil after the invasio=
n of Ukraine, it said that it =E2=80=9Cwill commit profits from the limited=
 amount of Russian oil we have to purchase to a dedicated fund=E2=80=9D tha=
t will be used =E2=80=9Cto alleviate the terrible consequences that this wa=
r is having on the people of Ukraine.=E2=80=9D (It has since decided to   s=
top buying Russian oil.) I suppose one could do the same thing with Russian=
 JVs: Put them in a special-purpose entity and escrow any proceeds to help =
Ukraine? In some loose sense the JV assets belong to the shareholders now, =
so it=E2=80=99s weird for the company to donate them, but that is loosely t=
rue of Shell=E2=80=99s oil trading profits too and that didn=E2=80=99t stop=
 it from donating them.=C2=A0Still elsewhere in oil:=09=E2=80=9CBiden Says =
U.S. Will   Ban Russian Fuels to Pressure Putin.=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CChina =
  Considers Buying Stakes in Russian Energy, Commodity Firms.=E2=80=9D=09=
=E2=80=9CThe Future Turns Dark for  Russia=E2=80=99s Oil Industry.=E2=80=9D=
=09=E2=80=9CRussian  tankers at sea despite =E2=80=98big unknown=E2=80=99 o=
ver who will buy oil.=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CMaduro hails =E2=80=98cordial=E2=
=80=99 talks with US as west seeks new oil supplies.=E2=80=9D
