   =20
      Oh Elon
   =20
 =20
It is not exactly my job to read Elon Musk=E2=80=99s tweets and decide whic=
h of them constitute securities fraud, but it is kind of=C2=A0my job. A thi=
ng that very much happens in my life is that Elon Musk  writes a tweet=C2=
=A0and like eight people send it to me asking =E2=80=9Cis this securities f=
raud?=E2=80=9D I cannot complain too much, there are definitely worse jobs =
and I have brought this upon myself, but it is not my favorite=C2=A0part of=
 the job. Elon Musk is very good at writing tweets that are debatably, a li=
ttle bit, maybe securities fraud, and the right way to respond to that is n=
ot to carefully parse which tweets fall on which side of the line but  rath=
er to say =E2=80=9Cthis is Elon Musk=E2=80=99s Twitter we are talking about=
 here, it is all gonna be pretty weird and you have to live with it.=E2=80=
=9DExcept for that one tweet about having funding secured to take Tesla Inc=
. private, that one was  pretty clearly securities fraud, that was fun.It o=
ccurs to me that=C2=A0the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission is in the=
 same position as I am, vis-=C3=A0-vis Musk=E2=80=99s Twitter?=09It is not =
really the SEC=E2=80=99s job to decide which of Musk=E2=80=99s tweets are s=
ecurities fraud.=09Except for the obvious big ones, like the =E2=80=9Cfundi=
ng secured=E2=80=9D one, you gotta punish that, and   the SEC did.=09Throug=
h some combination of conscious enthusiasm and historical accident,=C2=A0th=
e SEC has brought upon itself an expectation that it will parse all of Musk=
=E2=80=99s tweets.=09Perhaps it enjoys doing that but boy I doubt it. Anywa=
y:=C2=A0Tesla Inc. Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk asked a judge to end t=
he U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s oversight of his Twitt=
er posts under a 2018 agreement because he claims it is being used to =E2=
=80=9Ctrample=E2=80=9D his free speech rights.Musk also asked the judge to =
block an SEC subpoena for documents relating to the review of his tweets an=
d his sale of stock and options, a court filing on Tuesday showed. An SEC s=
pokesperson didn=E2=80=99t immediately respond to a request for comment.=C2=
=A0The SEC is investigating whether Musk and his brother Kimbal violated se=
curities laws when selling shares in the company late last year, according =
to a person familiar with the matter.Yeah look if I were the SEC lawyer in =
charge of parsing Musk=E2=80=99s tweets I would be absolutely desperate to =
move on with my life. I concede that the question of =E2=80=9Cwhether Musk =
and his brother Kimbal violated securities laws when selling shares in the =
company late last year=E2=80=9D is kind of an interesting one =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0we  discussed it last week =E2=80=94 and if I worked at the SEC I would =
want to keep digging on that one. But I=E2=80=99d probably let the consent =
decree go.=C2=A0
