      Pyramid scheme
   =20
 =20
Oh sure, sure:Since time immemorial, there has been something undeniably aw=
esome about gigantic pyramids. The Egyptians built them. The Aztecs built t=
hem. Even corporations have built them. But a DAO has never built a single =
one.It=E2=80=99s time to change that.We (Terran Robotics) are developing a =
drone-based 3D printing system that deploys monolithic adobe, the world=E2=
=80=99s lowest-cost building material.By combining automation with low mate=
rial costs, we can build an arbitrarily large structure at a much lower cos=
t than stone or concrete.The RealPyramidScheme DAO will decide collectively=
 on the design and location of the pyramid. The more we raise, the bigger i=
t will be.We project that costs will not exceed $75/m=C2=B3. For reference,=
 this translates to an absolute bargain of roughly $200 million USD to buil=
d the largest pyramid on Earth (1.5 meters taller than the Great Pyramid of=
 Giza).Let=E2=80=99s build.Is this a joke? I don=E2=80=99t know, and I don=
=E2=80=99t care much; many DAOs seem to be jokes without that stopping them=
 from being real. ConstitutionDAO never bought the Constitution but it=E2=
=80=99s still kicking around. Sure, build a pyramid, or at least raise a lo=
t of money to talk about it.
